Throughout my life, I have strived to be a law-abiding citizen and have learned from my past mistakes. I am a 54-year-old individual who has always taken my responsibilities seriously. This incident is completely out of character for me, and I am committed to making amends for my actions.

Although I understand the importance of pleading guilty to demonstrate acceptance of responsibility, I am open to alternative measures that the court deems appropriate to address the harm caused by my actions. While counseling may not be my preferred choice, I am willing to consider other forms of rehabilitation or intervention that the court sees fit.

Thank you, Your Honour, for allowing me the opportunity to address the court and share my remorse for my actions.

