Your Honour,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of being drunk and disorderly.

I take full responsibility for my actions and acknowledge that I was in the wrong. On the day in question, I made a poor decision to prioritize my own relaxation and disregard the impact it would have on others. I deeply regret my lack of control in that situation.

My name is Paul Nicholls, and I am 54 years old. I have lived a life striving to be a responsible and law-abiding citizen. Alongside this incident, I must acknowledge a previous conviction of careless driving from 10 years ago. Although these incidents are regrettable, I want to assure the court that they are not indicative of my overall character. I have learned from my previous mistakes and have taken steps to ensure that such behavior is not repeated.

I want the court to know that I am deeply ashamed of my actions. I regret my behavior and the trouble it may have caused. I understand the impact my actions may have had on others and I am committed to making amends for my actions and demonstrating that this incident is not representative of my character.

Thank you, Your Honour, for allowing me the opportunity to address the court and express my deep remorse for my actions.
